  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed unattached neighbour at No 66. Crow Lane benefits from a double storey rear extension within close proximity to the proposed subject property which would directly overlook into the rear garden environment of the proposed studio. This would fail to provide adequate levels of privacy within this amenity space causing considerable harm to the amenity of future occupants contrary to Policies 7, 26 of the Havering Local Plan and Policy D6 of the London Plan.",
    "The proposed dwelling, by reason of its proximity to neighbouring commercial uses and its design and layout, including the proximity of the main habitable room windows to the site frontage, would be likely to incur unreasonable adverse amenity impacts by reason of noise and disturbance, general pedestrian and vehicular activity, leading to a poor quality living environment to the detriment of the amentity of future occupiers, contrary to Policy 7of the Havering Local Plan.",
